glosses: to make; to build, construct, fashion; to create; to manufacture; to produce; to prepare
to do; to busy oneself with, act, behave

examples.translation: My father fixed the defective lamp.

etymology: Inherited from Ottoman Turkish یاپمق (yapmak, “to do, make, arrange”), from Proto-Turkic *yap- (“to make, create, arrange”). Cognate with Karakhanid [script needed] (yapmāq, “to build”), Old Uyghur [script needed] (yap-, “to make”).
